Happy Earth Day! We are celebrating the planetâs beauty with our FIRST EVER virtual scavenger hunt, with chances to win tickets to the Conservatory (when we reopen). The theme is rainbow, a symbol of hope during times of uncertainty. ð

To play:
1. Post a picture of the day's prompt on Instagram.
2. Include #fpcRainbow and tag @fpconservatory in the caption.

The challenge: Find an example of the following colors found in nature:
April 22: Red
April 23: Orange
April 24: Yellow
April 25: Green
April 26: Blue
April 27: Indigo
April 28: Purple

Make sure your profile is set to public so we can see your entries! Certain entries may be shared on the Conservatory's social media pages (with credit).

Have fun! ð

****IMPORTANT BUS INFORMATION!!! PLEASE READ BELOW******

"Attention Parents/Guardians, VERY IMPORTANT!!!! last week I sent a paper home regarding 2018-2019 Columbus City School busing with the students who live in the Columbus City School District. Hopefully you all are doing this on your own. I will not have a way of knowing if you did. I have offered times to help get you set up. A+ Children's Academy will no longer be sending in paperwork for you it is all done online now by you the parent/guardian. If you do not get it done this school year there will be a 6-8 week wait starting in August of 2018. Please act accordingly for 2018-2019 if you live in the Columbus City School District."
